str2: Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.

str2: To deceive, lie, speak falsely. Middle voice of an apparently primary verb; to utter an untruth or attempt to deceive by falsehood.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.

parse: Personal / Reciprocal Pronoun - Accusative Masculine Plural
str2: One another, each other. Genitive plural from allos reduplicated; one another.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Middle - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: To strip, divest, renounce. Middle voice from apo and ekduo; to divest wholly oneself, or despoil.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Old, ancient, not new or recent. From palai; antique, i.e. Not recent, worn out.
A man, one of the human race. From aner and ops; man-faced, i.e. A human being.
With. A primary preposition denoting union; with or together.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
From prasso; practice, i.e. an act; by extension, a function.
